        <main class="main" id="main" tabindex="-1">
            <div class="container">

                
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-12">

                            <!-- Must reside outside the <h1> tag, as divs are not allowed in <h1>'s -->
                            <h1 class="or-page-title">
                                
	

                                Contracts and Procurement
                            </h1>
                            <div class="form-group or-show-if-side-navigation">
                                <button class="btn btn-default btn-block hidden-md hidden-lg hidden-xl" type="button" data-toggle="offcanvas" data-target="#OregonSideNavigation" data-canvas="body"><span class="fa fa-bars notranslate" aria-hidden="true"></span> <span>Site Navigation</span></button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    

                    

                    
	

                    <!--Sharepoint's placeholder-->

                    
	
	
	

	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-9 pers-content-with-aside">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField1_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField1__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ><h2>About Us<br></h2><p>Contracts and Procurement, a part of the Central Business Support Section at Oregon PERS, conducts all purchases of
    goods and services for the agency.</p><h2 id="howto">How to do business with PERS</h2><p>PERS contracting and procurement processes are subject to the rules and regulations of the Oregon Public Procurement
    Code in Oregon Revised Statute (ORS) 279. Contracts are established through a variety of solicitation methods,
    including Invitation to Bid (ITB), Request for Proposal (RFP), and Request for Quotes (RFQ). </p><p> Vendors wishing to speak with a PERS buyer should contact the procurement assistant at 503-603-7505 or
    <a href="mailto&#58;PERS-Procurement.Office@pers.oregon.gov">PERS-Procurement.Office@pers.oregon.gov</a>.
</p><h2 id="options">Contracting options</h2><p>The Oregon Department of Administrative Services (DAS)/Enterprise Goods and Services State Procurement Section grants
    PERS purchasing authority based upon the monetary value of the resultant contract. Solicitations valued at more than
    $10,000 are publicly advertised in State of Oregon's Purchasing Information Network (ORPIN). A summary of that
    authority includes&#58; </p><p>
    <strong>$9,999 or Less</strong>
</p><p> Procurement has discretion to purchase and/or contract without obtaining competitive quotes for these purchases. For
    procurements between $5,000 and $9,999, notices will be posted in ORPIN and with the Director of Economic and
    Business Equity for Oregon Minority, Women, and Emerging Small Business (OMWESB). </p><p>
    <strong>$10,000 to $149,999</strong>
</p><p> Procurement may purchase and/or contract within these thresholds by obtaining at least three competitive quotes for
    these procurements. Notification to the Oregon Minority, Women, and Emerging Small Business (OMWESB) is also
    required. </p><p>
    <strong>More than $150,000</strong>
</p><p> The Oregon Public Procurement Code requires formal competition for all contracts over $150,000. All solicitations
    are advertised on the ORPIN system. Notification to the Oregon Minority, Women, and Emerging Small Business (OMWESB)
    is also required.</p><h2 id="types">Types of contracting opportunities</h2><p>PERS uses a variety of goods and services that fulfill needs of both our agency and our customers, focusing on
    services to maintain our benefits database and ensure accuracy in our services. </p><p>Opportunities include&#58;</p><ul><li> IT consulting and programming </li><li> IT hardware and software </li><li> Trade services to support facilities operations and maintenance </li><li> Courier </li><li> Mail presort </li><li> Medical documentation review </li><li> Health insurance consulting and third-party administrator services </li><li> Deferred compensation consulting and third-party administration services </li></ul><h2 id="current">Current contracting opportunities</h2><p>To see contract opportunities for PERS and other state agencies, go to the State Procurement Office website (<a href="/DAS/EGS/PS/pages/index.aspx">www.oregon.gov/DAS/EGS/PS/pages/index.aspx</a>), and under &quot;ORPIN
    Information&quot; and &quot;Using ORPIN to Find Business Opportunities,&quot; click on the Log in to ORPIN button.
</p><p>On the ORPIN login page, click on the Browse link in the left sidebar, and then click on the Browse Opportunities
    link. Here you can choose to search for solicitations by Open Opportunities, By Organization, or By Product/Service.
</p><h2 id="contact">Contact us</h2>
<strong>Physical address&#58;</strong><br> PERS-PPO
<br> 11410 SW 68th Parkway
<br> Tigard, OR 97223
<br><br><strong>Mailing address&#58;</strong><br> PERS-PPO
<br> PO Box 23700
<br> Tigard, OR 97281-3700
<br> Toll free&#58; 888-320-PERS
<br> Fax&#58; 503-598-0561
<br> TTY&#58; 503-603-7766
<p>
    <strong>Phone hours&#58; 8&#58;30 a.m. - 4 p.m.</strong>
</p><p>Procurement assistance&#58; phone 503-603-7505 or email
    <a href="mailto&#58;PERS-Procurement.Office@pers.oregon.gov">PERS-Procurement.Office@pers.oregon.gov</a>.
</p><h2 id="resources">Resources</h2><p>Department of Administrative Services-Oregon Procurement Information Network (ORPIN) </p><p> To learn about all contracting opportunities with the state of Oregon, go to the ORPIN website at
    <a href="http&#58;//orpin.oregon.gov/">http&#58;//orpin.oregon.gov</a>.
</p><p>
    <strong>Office of Minority, Women, and Emerging Small Business (OMWESB)</strong>
</p><p> To register as a minority, women-owned, or emerging small business for state funded projects, go to the Office of
    Minority, Women, and Emerging Small Business website at
    <a href="http&#58;//www.oregon4biz.com/How-We-Can-Help/OMWESB/">http&#58;//www.oregon4biz.com/How-We-Can-Help/OMWESB/</a>.
</p><p>
    <strong>Oregon Public Procurement Code</strong>
</p><p>
    <a href="/DAS/EGS/ps/Pages/index.aspx">http&#58;//www.oregon.gov/DAS/EGS/ps/Pages/index.aspx</a>.
</p></div>
				</div>
			</div>

